< text>
We were driving for hours and needed a place to stop and eat something. Based on the reviews, Chow's kitchen in Kingsburg was the place to go. My bf had wor won ton soup and I had a chicken chow mein. The portions were big and the food was so good. The only downfall if you wanted to order a combo item is that they all have some sort of pork in it. If you don't eat pork then your only option is to pick a non-combo item. They had great service, and the restaurant was nice and clean inside. I definitely would recommend anyone to try it! Chow's kitchen was delicious. Thanks so much!!!!</text>

<Review>What a great dinner we had here. There were 4 of us and we went to dinner around 6 PM on Sunday. It was nice and quite, not busy at all. The waitress was nice and wasn't too bothersome, she checked on us just the right number of times. Didn't interrupt our conversation and kept the drinks filled. The food was awesome. We had 2 orders of orange chicken, 1 egg foo young, and 1 teriyaki chicken combo. The combos are great as they come with chow mein and pork fried rice. My favorite is the teriyaki chicken and my wife really likes the egg foo young. Everyone was very happy with their orders. Haven't had a bad meal here yet. On occasion if its busy it can get a little loud in here, the sound really bounces around the dining area there.</Review>< gmapID>

<userid>103042924538678656074<//userid><username>Da Honu</username><Time>1588112858794< /Time><Rating>5<//Rating>< text>
When I first started looking for screens for my French Patio doors. I looked at several different brands. However I kept coming back to Clearview.  Main reason was for the speed reduced. With you grandkids, I wanted something safe.

Sarah at the office was very nice and understood what I wanted. I was out of their area and referred me to a local guy, but he wasn‚Äôt installing anymore. No problem Sarah to the rescue talked to her boss and he agreed to come out.

Today (4/28/2020) Shawn showed up, introduced himself and started working. He was very efficient and fast. He cleaned up after the install and even vacuumed any small fragments from the install. Once he was done he showed me how the door functions, how the one side (left) can stay shut and locked into place. I opted for the internal magnets and the standard nylon door handle.

Shawn left me with stickers to prevent people from walking through it and left me with a bottle of track silicone lube to make sure the screens keep moving smooth.

I am so happy I chose ClearView.

I will update this next year.</text>

< text>
I am writing this review before the product is installed and the rating reflects the way the whole process has been managed to date.

I called to get an appointment set up for someone to come out and see what options were available to me and discuss pricing. I was given a time 2 weeks out on a Saturday with a specific time of 12:00 PM; not a window of time but a specific time. On the day of the appointment at 12:58 PM, I called ClearView office and I asked if someone was still coming out and at 1:20 PM I received a call from the tech saying he is running late and will be there in 20 minutes. He showed up just before 2 PM and spent about 15 minutes there discussing the options and collecting the 50% down payment on 2 doors.

On the following Monday, I received a call scheduling the install for a Saturday, 3 weeks out, which is in about 3 days from when I am writing this review for 1:30 PM; again, not a window of time but a specific time. Today, I get a call saying that they need to "pull back" the appointment by a little bit to 3 PM! I think they meant push out to 3 PM, so I called to see what happened and after going through the Abbott & Costello routine with the first person who answered the call getting no logical response for the push out, she had me speak with another person who told me they are very busy this summer and that the same guy that was late the last time will be out between 3 & 5 PM on Saturday! Wait, until now everything has been a specific time, now it is a window of time 3 days before the appointment and I have to change my plans for Saturday to accommodate their poor or inept scheduling management. She said we have too many appointments scheduled for Saturday morning and didn't want to be late so they pushed my appointment out. In other words, they squeezed another 1 or 2 appointments in pushing me out because "we are very busy this summer"!

The experience to date has not been very good and I am hoping the quality of product and installation is not horrible because "it has been a very busy summer" for ClearView. Clearly, customer service is not their concern!</text>

Due to COVID-19 once going inside you get in line and tell the employee what size bowl you want regular or large and then they ask about how much and what kind of yogurt you want. Option is 1/4 , 2/4 , 3/4 (a little more than halfway or 4/4 all the way filled) then they hand it over to someone else who will assist in putting the toppings for you. The bowl will then be placed in a weighing scale to determine your price. Lastly you can always ask for a lid.< /Review>

< text>
This is a good place when you're looking for several random things as there's a variety of stores here. I would steer clear of the toys as I've noticed they are priced higher compared to outside locations,but then again if you see something you haven't seen elsewhere,  i say pick it up.

The variety of stores includes, threading services, jewelry, pets, bikes, shoes, makeup, nail services, barber, braiding, food, clothing, party supplies, florist and so many more. I remeber seeing 2 locations offering piercings and my favorite was the crystal/stone stores.

Definitely ceck it out and have a good time walking around and see what you find. I got my pink salt lampt there that came with a blue tint light. Currently enjoying it at home.</text>

< text>
I love shopping here. The only 2 downfalls I see are trying to find what area the things you need would be in. I think they need more directories and/or categorising of the shops so you know all auto here, shoes here ect..
The people were very friendly for the most part. I did run into a couple of rude sales clerks.
The lady at the wig shop is extremely kind and very helpful.
My second issue is if you are using a wheelchair or walker you can not get into mist shops. The aisles are to narrow.
I will shop there again and I do recommend this place if you are looking for bargains and aren't we all, lol.<//text>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< Name>
Casey Luyben<//Name>
< review>
Full of cultural diversity and buzzing with the smell of money and cheap replicated leather, the swap meet of Pomona is a dirty, grungy, beautiful landmark in the outskirts of this God forsaken city. Find most things you may need walking shop to shop, and everything you absolutely do not, but don't let it fool you. These shop keeps know their way around a haggle and are not afraid to press your pocket book. Happy hunting and keep your eyes open, for there is always someone waiting for you to slip up. Only in Pomona!< /review>

< Text>
There is variety of items:  bicycles, skateboards, all kinds of toys, music, gold jewelry, Mexican candies, guayabera style shirts, all kinds of clothes from casual to fancy items, pet items.  Great place to purchase Baptism items, quinceanera stuff.  The food place in the middle has really good fresh Mexican food.  The churros by the front exit are so good.  I got a churro with caramel filling and it was very tasty.  Some of the shops only take cash, no credit or debit cards; there is an ATM machine in the back but I do not remember what they charge.    They have a portrait studio that has been there for many years, the photographers are very good.</Text>
